## Definitions

**"Mod"** means VS Shields in the form of source code, compiled JAR files, or any part thereof.

**"Official JAR"** means a compiled binary published by the author on Modrinth or GitHub Releases.

**"Fork"** means any public or private copy of the Mod's repository, excluding automatic forks created by GitHub as part of a Pull Request workflow.

**"Derivative Work"** means any software that incorporates more than 15 consecutive lines of the Mod's source code, or any complete class or method from the Mod.

**"Modpack"** means a collection of mods and configuration files distributed together for Minecraft.

**"Written Permission"** means explicit written consent from the author, obtained via email or GitHub (Issues or Discussions).

**"Credit"** means a visible mention of the mod name "VS Shields", the author "LennyPane", and a link to the official GitHub repository.

## Restrictions

**No Forking Without Permission.** You may not create, publish, or maintain a Fork of the Mod without Written Permission from the author.

**No Modified Binaries.** You may not distribute, publish, or otherwise make available any modified version of the Mod's compiled JAR files.

**No Code Reuse.** You may not copy, incorporate, or adapt code from the Mod into other mods or software projects in a way that constitutes a Derivative Work, without Written Permission.

**No Commercial Use.** You may not sell, sublicense, or otherwise commercially exploit the Mod, its source code, or any Derivative Work. Monetization of Forks or modifications is prohibited.

**No Removal of Attribution.** You may not remove, alter, or obscure any copyright notice or author attribution present in the source code or compiled files.

## Permitted Uses

**Modpack Inclusion.** You may include the Mod in any Modpack, including commercially monetized Modpacks, provided that: (a) only an unmodified Official JAR is used; (b) Credit is given in the Modpack's description, README, or equivalent listing; and (c) a link to the official GitHub repository is included.

**Server Use.** Any Minecraft server, including servers that accept donations, subscriptions, or other payments, may use the Mod without additional permission. Server monetization is not a violation of this license, so long as the Mod itself is not sold.

**Viewing and Learning.** You may view, read, and study the Mod's source code on GitHub for educational and reference purposes.

**Contributions.** Pull Requests to the official repository are welcome. By submitting a contribution, you grant the author a perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide license to use, modify, and distribute your contribution as part of the Mod under the terms of this license. You retain the right to reuse your own contributed code in other projects.

